## 🚀 The Authentication Implementation

Here is how the main functional blocks of the authentication system are structured:

### 1. Route Gating via Middleware
We protect all dashboard pages using the SDK's Edge-compatible middleware helper:
```typescript
// middleware.ts
import { relipayMiddleware } from '@relipay/nextjs/middleware';

export default relipayMiddleware({
  publicRoutes: ['/', '/login', '/register'], // Allow unauthenticated access
  signInUrl: '/login', // Redirect unauthenticated users here
});

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!_next|.*\\..*).*)'],
};
```

### 2. Register & Login (React 19 Server Actions)
We kept credential verification entirely on the server using Next.js Server Actions. Using React 19's `useActionState` in client components, we wired up clean user feedback for loading and error states:

```typescript
// app/register/actions.ts
'use server';

import { signUp } from '@relipay/nextjs/server';
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';

export async function registerAction(prevState: any, formData: FormData) {
  const email = formData.get('email')?.toString().trim();
  const password = formData.get('password')?.toString();

  if (!email || !password) return { error: 'Credentials required.' };

  try {
    // Sets encrypted HttpOnly session cookies automatically on success
    await signUp({ email, password });
  } catch (err: any) {
    return { error: err.message || 'Registration failed.' };
  }
  redirect('/dashboard');
}
```

### 3. Gated Dashboard & Sign Out
On our server-component dashboard page, we fetch the active session details using the server-side `auth()` helper, which automatically validates or refreshes the access token:

```typescript
// app/dashboard/page.tsx
import { auth } from '@relipay/nextjs/server';
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const session = await auth();
  if (!session) redirect('/login');

  const { user } = session;
  return <h1>Welcome, {user.email}</h1>;
}
```
Logging out is handled via `signOut()` imported from `@relipay/nextjs/server`, which instantly clears the secure browser session cookies.

